definition.value: A prenylglycerol phosphate that consists of 1-phosphoglycerol having an all-trans-pentaprenyl group attached at position 3; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A prenylglycerol phosphate that consists of 1-phosphoglycerol having two all-trans-pentaprenyl groups attached at position 2 and 3; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
The zwitterionic form of 2-aminoisobutyric acid obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of L-valine; major species at pH 7.3.
A menaquinol whose structure comprises a 2-methylbenzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of four isoprenoid units.
A quadruply-charged carboxyalkyl phosphate oxoanion resulting from global deprotonation of O-phospho-3-sulfolactic acid; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An anthocyanidin D-galactoside having the galactosyl residue at the 3-position attached via a beta-linkage.
The conjugate base of methylcarbamic acid; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A primary amine protonated on nitrogen bound to carbon with two alkyl chains.
Conjugate acid of (R)-laudanosoline arising from protonation of the isoquinoline nitrogen; major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-[(4-amino-3,5-dichloro-6-fluoropyridin-2-yl)oxy]propanoic acid with the hydroxy group of tetrahydrofuran-2-ylmethanol.
